&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Join Our Talent Community!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 16.5pt; margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt 0in;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: black;&quot;&gt;Thank you for your interest in Tarsus Pharmaceuticals!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;We&#39;re always looking for future Tarsans and regularly update our Careers page with currently open positions. Major growth is expected following the recent announcement of our Saturn-1 clinical trial results, and many new roles are on the horizon. If you don&#39;t see what you&#39;re looking for at the moment, please feel free to apply to Tarsus by attaching your résumé and letting us know a little about yourself! Our Talent Acquisition team will keep you in mind for future job openings.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;And, don&#39;t forget to follow us on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/company/tarsus-pharmaceuticals-inc/posts/?feedView=all&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;LinkedIn&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt; for the latest company updates and job opportunities!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Tarsus Pharmaceuticals, Inc. is an Equal Opportunity Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex including sexual orientation and gender identity, national origin, disability, protected Veteran Status, or any other characteristic protected by applicable federal, state, or local law.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Manager II, Compliance will partner with the Compliance Department in developing, implementing, and maintaining an effective Compliance Program that (1) supports and promotes a Companywide culture of ethics and compliance, and (2) meets or exceeds applicable regulatory standards for effective compliance programs, including the Office of Inspector General (OIG) Guidance, the U.S. Sentencing Guidelines, and the Department of Justice guidance.&amp;nbsp; As a member of a collaborative team, this role will contribute to the development, implementation, and maintenance of all elements of the Tarsus Compliance program.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Let’s talk about some of the key responsibilities of the role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the execution lead for the end-to-end transparency reporting process, including oversight of applicable federal and state reporting requirements, partnering with internal stakeholders to ensure accurate data collection and review, managing external vendor relationships, delivering training, and maintaining supporting systems to ensure timely and compliant submissions.&lt;/li&gt;
